  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 12.06,
      "end": 21.1,
      "text": "The Lion and the Ass.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 21.1,
      "end": 26.68,
      "text": "Chapter IV A Lion and an Ass set up as partners and went",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 26.68,
      "end": 32.06,
      "text": "to hunting together. In course of time they came to a cave in which there was a number of",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 32.06,
      "end": 38.04,
      "text": "wild goats. The lion took up his stand at the mouth of the cave and waited for them to come",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 38.04,
      "end": 43.72,
      "text": "out. While the Ass went inside and braid for all he was worth in order to frighten them out into",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 43.72,
      "end": 50.12,
      "text": "the open, the lion struck them down one by one as they appeared, and when the cave was empty,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 50.12,
      "end": 56.0,
      "text": "the Ass came out and said, well I scared them pretty well, didn't I? I should think you did,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 56.2,
      "end": 60.98,
      "text": "said the lion. Why, if I hadn't known you were an Ass, I should have turned and run myself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 62.94,
      "end": 65.98,
      "text": "End of the Lion and the Ass.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
